trPosition":"Defender","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.92 m (6 ft 4 in)","strWeight":"","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/v58pbd1767626049.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/fnl0821767626110.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":null,"strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Silva"},{"idPlayer":"34219131","idTeam":"134736","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"41544","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":null,"idESPN":null,"strNationality":"Brazil","strPlayer":"Eduardo Santos","strPlayerAlternate":"Eduardo Gonzaga Mendes Santos","strTeam":"Bragantino","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"1997-11-28","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"São Paulo, Brazil","strEthnicity":"Hispanic","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Eduardo Gonzaga Mendes Santos (born 28 November 1997) is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays as a centre-back for Red Bull Bragantino.\r\n\r\nCareer\r\nSantos began his career at the age of 13, signing for Fluminense, after initially playing street football. After a short spell at Juventus da Mooca, Santos rejoined Fluminense for a fee of R$415,310 in 2017. At Fluminense, Santos was loaned out in 2018 to Portuguese LigaPro sides Real, where he made 16 league appearances, and Famalicão, where he made one league appearance. In 2019, Santos was loaned to Brazilian Série B club São Bento, making four league appearances during his time at the club.\r\n\r\nIn 2020, Santos left Fluminense to join Capivariano, before joining Czech club Karviná on loan alongside fellow Capivariano player Jean Mangabeira. After nine league appearances for Karviná in the 2019–20 Czech First League season, Santos made his move to the club permanent ahead of the following season. On 21 February 2022, after 57 appearances and three goals in all competitions for Karviná, Viktoria Plzeň announced the signing of Santos on a six-month loan. Santos made ten appearances as Viktoria Plzeň won the Czech First League for the first time since 2018. On 11 June 2022, Slavia Prague announced the signing of Santos on a four-year contract. In April 2023, he returned on loan to Brazil with Red Bull Bragantino until December. On 8 December 2023, Red Bull Bragantino activate option on Santos and signed him on permanent deal.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Defender","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.96 m (6 ft 5 in)","strWeight":"","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/adpjbi1766834153.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/ojakce1766834070.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/ur5jyg1766834193.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Santos"},{"idPlayer":"34219136","idTeam":"134736","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"10004","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":null,"idESPN":null,"strNationality":"Brazil","strPlayer":"Eduardo Sasha","strPlayerAlternate":"Eduardo Colcenti Antunes","strTeam":"Bragantino","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"1992-02-24","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Porto Alegre, Brazil","strEthnicity":"Hispanic","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Eduardo Colcenti Antunes (born 24 February 1992), known as Eduardo Sasha or simply Sasha, is a Brazilian footballer who plays as a forward for Red Bull Bragantino.\r\n\r\nHe made his professional debut for Internacional in 2010, and has won the Campeonato Gaúcho four times for the club. He spent 18 months on loan at Goiás, where he won the Campeonato Brasileiro Série B and the Campeonato Goiano. In 2018 he moved to Santos. In 2020, Sasha joined Atlético Mineiro, winning the Campeonato Brasileiro Série A and the Copa do Brasil in 2021, among other titles.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Attacker","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.73 m (5 ft 8 in)","strWeight":"70 kg","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/kzfypz1766835060.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/ifjyhc1766835102.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/amj8xe1766835154.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"Yes","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Sasha"},{"idPlayer":"34225993","idTeam":"134736","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"10027","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":null,"idESPN":null,"strNationality":"Brazil","strPlayer":"Eric Ramires","strPlayerAlternate":"Eric dos Santos Rodrigues","strTeam":"Bragantino","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"2000-08-10","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Salvador, Brazil","strEthnicity":"Hispanic","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Eric dos Santos Rodrigues (born 10 August 2000), known as Eric Ramires or Ramires, is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Red Bull Bragantino.\r\n\r\nClub career\r\nBahia\r\nBorn in Salvador, Bahia, Ramires joined Bahia's youth setup in 2011. He played regularly for the under-15 and under-17 sides, going on to win the Copa Red Ball, Copa Dois de Julho and Copa Metropolitana.\r\n\r\nOn 6 September 2018, Eric Ramires made his first team – and Série A – debut, starting in a 2–0 victory over Sport; by doing so, he became the first player born in 2000 to play for the club. On 15 September, his contract was extended until 2022.\r\n\r\nOn 21 September 2018, Ramires made his Copa Sudamericana debut, starting and scoring the opener in a 2–1 home defeat of Botafogo.\r\n\r\nBasel\r\nOn 2 September 2019, Ramires da Silva signed with Swiss club Basel. The club announced the loan for their 2019–20 season under manager Marcel Koller on their home page on that day. He played his domestic league debut for the club in the home game at the St. Jakob-Park on 25 September as Basel won 4–0 against Zürich. He was substituted in for the last seven minutes of the match.\r\n\r\nThe club announced that the contract with Ramires would not be prolonged on 5 September 2020. During his one season with the club Ramires played a total of 12 games for Basel without scoring a goal. Nine of these games were in the Swiss Super League, two in the UEFA Europa League and one was a friendly game.\r\n\r\nInternational career\r\nOn 13 December 2018, Ramires was included in Brazil under-20s for the 2019 South American U-20 Championship.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Midfielder","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"1.72 m (5 ft 8 in)","strWeight":"65 kg","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/08jqnb1767202826.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/p6wrg71767202912.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/8yadpq1767202961.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Ramires"},{"idPlayer":"34222523","idTeam":"134736","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"279805","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":null,"idESPN":null,"strNationality":"Brazil","strPlayer":"Fabinho","strPlayerAlternate":"Fábio Silva de Freitas","strTeam":"Bragantino","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"2002-04-09","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Natal, Brazil","strEthnicity":"Hispanic","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Fábio Silva de Freitas (born 9 April 2002), commonly known as Fabinho, is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays as a defensive midfielder for Campeonato Brasileir